% layout 'default';
% title '$HOME/notes - Know, How and Example. 3 simple knowledge base';
<div class="contents">
    <div class="row-search">
        <div class="row row-fluid">
            <div class="span12 search-form">
                <div class="form-inline">
                    <label class="checkbox">
                        <input name="check" value="know" type="checkbox" checked><small> in Know </small>
                    </label>
                    <label class="checkbox">
                        <input name="check" value="how" type="checkbox"><small> in How </small> 
                    </label>
                    <label class="checkbox">
                        <input name="check" value="example" type="checkbox"><small> in Example </small> 
                    </label>
                    <br>
                    <div class="input-append">
                        <input id="search_text" type="text">
                        <button id="search" class="btn" type="submit">Search</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_info">
        <h1> $HOME/notes </h1>
        <p> 
        This is a knowledge base which stores limited number of characters.<br>
        Simply dividing into 3 categories - Know, How and Example. <br>
        <br>
        <%== $share_button %>
        </p>
        <!-- Button to trigger modal or share knowledge button -->
    </div>
    <div class="container"> 
    <div id="view">
        <div class="row pagination-centered">
            <div class="span4">
                <h2>Get the point <i class="icon-lightbulb"></i></h2>
              <p>Knowhow is stored as three simple catetories, know, how and example. And each has limited number of characters. 
                 For this, the contents can become easily to read, understand and more importantly you can find the one you want.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="span4">
              <h2>Find knowhow <i class="icon-search"></i> </h2>
              <p>You can find the knowhow by the category. <a href="/taglist">#tag</a> also can be used. If you add '@name' in search text, the knowhow owned by him/her shows up.
                 After logging in, you can add knowhow. Share your knowhow and make people's life easy :)
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="span4">
                <h2>Stock knowhow <i class="icon-share"></i></h2>
              <p>Once you logged in, you can add other's knowhow into yours so that it becomes your knowhow. 
                 You will search it easily with '@twitter_screenname" next time. 
              </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    </div>


    <!-- Modal -->
    <div id="myModal" class="modal hide fade" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-header">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">Ã—</button>
        </div>
        <div class="modal-body">
            <h3>Know <span class="count" id="know_count"></span> </h3>
            <textarea class="input-size" row="1" id="know"></textarea> 
            <br>            
            <h3>How <span class="count" id="how_count"></span></h3>
            <textarea class="input-size" row="1" id="how"></textarea> 
            <h3>Example <span class="count" id="example_count"></span></h3>
            <textarea class="example-size" id="example" rows="5"></textarea>
        </div>
        <div class="modal-footer">
            <button class="btn" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">Close</button>
            <button id="submit" class="btn btn-warning">Submit your knowhow!</button>
        </div>
    </div>
    <!-- END OF Modal -->

    <br>
    <div class="footer">
    <p>&copy; iworld designer 2013</p>
    </div>

</div>


